  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDescribedObject  
    CardinalityConstraint
    Represents a constraint based on the cardinality of some item.
    DomainProfile
    A profile contains information about how to organize objects in some domain into a tree and perform operations on it.
    NodeConstraint
    A node constraint represents requirements on a node.
    NodeTransform
    Represents a transform of a node Each transform has a source, a result, possibly an action, and a description.
    NodeType
    The type of a node explains how to map a node to a domain object.
    Property
    A property has a value and a type.
    PropertyCategory
    Represents a group of related properties.
    PropertyConstraint
    A PropertyConstraint represents restrictions on the cardinality and type of a property in a node.
    PropertyType
    The type of a property explains how to map a property to a domain object.
    StructuralRelation
    Represents a pair of symmetric of domain predicates used to connect domain objects.
